
Overview of verb afflict

The verb afflict has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                      
1. afflict -- (cause great unhappiness for; distress; "she was afflicted by the death of her parents")
2. afflict, smite -- (cause physical pain or suffering in; "afflict with the plague")

